#. Tag: title
#: lxc.xml:206
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring IP Addresses for Network Interfaces"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: lxc.xml:207
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Network devices and hostdev devices with network capabilities can be "
"provided with one or more IP addresses to set on the network device in the "
"guest. However, some hypervisors or network device types will simply ignore "
"them or only use the first one."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: lxc.xml:220
#, no-c-format
msgid "The following example shows how to set one ore multiple IP addresses:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: #text
#: lxc.xml:224
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"[...]&lt;devices&gt; &lt;interface type='network'&gt; &lt;source "
"network='default'/&gt; &lt;target dev='vnet0'/&gt; &lt;ip "
"address='192.168.122.5' prefix='24'/&gt; &lt;ip address='192.168.122.5' "
"prefix='24' peer"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: #text
#: lxc.xml:230
#, no-c-format
msgid "='192.168.122.0' prefix"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: #text
#: lxc.xml:230
#, no-c-format
msgid "='10.0.0.10'/&gt; &lt;route family"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: #text
#: lxc.xml:231
#, no-c-format
msgid "='24' gateway"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: #text
#: lxc.xml:232
#, no-c-format
msgid "='192.168.122.1'/&gt; &lt;route family"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: #text
#: lxc.xml:232
#, no-c-format
msgid "='ipv4' address"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: #text
#: lxc.xml:233
#, no-c-format
msgid "='192.168.122.8' gateway"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: #text
#: lxc.xml:235
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"='192.168.122.1'/&gt; &lt;/interface&gt; [...] &lt;hostdev "
"mode='capabilities' type='net'&gt; &lt;source&gt; &lt;interface&gt;eth0&lt;/"
"interface&gt; &lt;/source&gt; &lt;ip address='192.168.122.6' prefix='24'/"
"&gt; &lt;route family='ipv4' address='192.168.122.0' prefix='24' "
"gateway='192.168.122.1'/&gt; &lt;route family='ipv4' address='192.168.122.8' "
"gateway='192.168.122.1'/&gt; &lt;/hostdev&gt;&lt;/devices&gt;[...]"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: lxc.xml:249
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Optional attribute. Holds the IP address of the other end of a point-to-"
"point network device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: lxc.xml:255
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Can be set to either <literal>ipv4</literal> or <literal>ipv6</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: lxc.xml:260
#, no-c-format
msgid "Contains the IP address."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: lxc.xml:265
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Optional parameter (will be automatically set if not specified). Defines the "
"number of 1 bits in the netmask. For IPv4, the default prefix is determined "
"according to the network <quote>class</quote> ( <literal>A</literal> , "
"<literal>B</literal> , or <literal>C</literal> ). For IPv6, the default "
"prefix is <literal>64</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: lxc.xml:274
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you do not specify a default gateway in the XML file, none will be set."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: lxc.xml:281
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also add route elements to define IP routes to add in the guest. "
"This is used by the LXC driver."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: #text
#: lxc.xml:286
#, no-c-format
msgid "[...]&lt;devices&gt; &lt;interface type"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: #text
#: lxc.xml:288
#, no-c-format
msgid "='ethernet'&gt; &lt;source/&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: #text
#: lxc.xml:289
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;ip address"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: #text
#: lxc.xml:290
#, no-c-format
